headline: 1 Consumer Stock with Promising Prospects and 2 to Steer Clear Of
summary: Consumer discretionary businesses are levered to the highs and lows of economic cycles. This sensitive demand profile can cause discretionary stocks to plummet when macro uncertainty enters the fray, and over the past six months, the industry has shed 7%. This performance was worse than the S&P 500’s 2.4% fall.
